        "title": "feat: add retries field to HealthCheckRunContext for transient failure handling",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Added `retries?: number` field to `HealthCheckRunContext` interface\n- Allows health checks to retry on transient failures before giving up\n\n## Problem\nTransient failures in health checks (network timeouts, temporary file locks) would immediately fail without retry opportunities.\n\n## Solution\nAdded optional `retries` field to `HealthCheckRunContext`:\n- Default: undefined (no retries, existing behavior)\n- When set, enables retry logic for transient failures\n\n## Testing\n- Type-only change, existing tests pass\n- No runtime behavior change without explicit usage",
